                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4214: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-27T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 27, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 27—1:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Referring to my telegram No. 41, June 27, 11 a.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d816fn9"
                        >Not printed.</note> Proclamation today by General Mittelhauser reads as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“By virtue of the armistice conditions signed by the French Government,
                            no change has taken place in the situation of the territory under
                            mandate.</p>
                        <p>Consequently the general commander in chief of the theater of operations
                            in the Eastern Mediterranean, in agreement with the High <pb facs="0906"
                                n="894" xml:id="pg_894"/> Commissioner, has ordered the cessation of
                            hostilities. The French flag will continue to fly over this territory
                            and France will pursue her mission in the Levant States.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Comment will follow by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Palmer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
